cs.LG, cs.AI, q-bio.BM, q-bio.QM, cs.NE

The paper proposes a new algorithm for the RNA Design problem using deep reinforcement learning, which falls under the intersection of computer science and bioinformatics. The use of deep reinforcement learning suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the focus on designing RNA molecules suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of q-bio.BM (Biomolecules) and q-bio.QM (Quantitative Methods). Additionally, the paper involves optimizing over a rich space of architectures and hyperparameters, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
